400.name: Bad Request
400.description: The browser (or proxy) sent a request that this server could not understand.

401.name: Unauthorized
401.description: The server could not verify that you are authorized to access the URL requested.  You either supplied the wrong credentials (e.g. a bad password), or your browser doesn't understand how to supply the credentials required.

403.name: Forbidden
403.description: You don't have the permission to access the requested resource. It is either read-protected or not readable by the server.

404.name: Not Found
404.description: The requested URL was not found on the server.  If you entered the URL manually please check your spelling and try again.

405.name: Method Not Allowed
405.description: The method is not allowed for the requested URL.

406.name: Not Acceptable
406.description: The resource identified by the request is only capable of generating response entities which have content characteristics not acceptable according to the accept headers sent in the request.

408.name: Request Timeout
408.description: The server closed the network connection because the browser didn't finish the request within the specified time.

409.name: Conflict
409.description: A conflict happened while processing the request.  The resource might have been modified while the request was being processed.

410.name: Gone
410.description: The requested URL is no longer available on this server and there is no forwarding address. If you followed a link from a foreign page, please contact the author of this page.

411.name: Length Required
411.description: A request with this method requires a valid Content-Length header.

412.name: Precondition Failed
412.description: The precondition on the request for the URL failed positive evaluation.

413.name: Request Entity Too Large
413.description: The data value transmitted exceeds the capacity limit.

414.name: Request URI Too Long
414.description: The length of the requested URL exceeds the capacity limit for this server.  The request cannot be processed.

415.name: Unsupported Media Type
415.description: The server does not support the media type transmitted in the request.

416.name: Requested Range Not Satisfiable
416.description: The server cannot provide the requested range.

417.name: Expectation Failed
417.description: The server could not meet the requirements of the Expect header

418.name: I'm a teapot
418.description: This server is a teapot, not a coffee machine

422.name: Unprocessable Entity
422.description: The request was well-formed but was unable to be followed due to semantic errors.

423.name: Locked
423.description: The resource that is being accessed is locked.

428.name: Precondition Required
428.description: This request is required to be conditional; try using "If-Match" or "If-Unmodified-Since".

429.name: Too Many Requests
429.description: This user has exceeded an allotted request count. Try again later.

431.name: Request Header Fields Too Large
431.description: One or more header fields exceeds the maximum size.

500.name: Internal Server Error
500.description: The server encountered an internal error and was unable to complete your request.  Either the server is overloaded or there is an error in the application.

501.name: Not Implemented
501.description: The server does not support the action requested by the browser.

502.name: Bad Gateway
502.description: The proxy server received an invalid response from an upstream server.

503.name: Service Unavailable
503.description: The server is temporarily unable to service your request due to maintenance downtime or capacity problems.  Please try again later.

504.name: Gateway Timeout
504.description: The connection to an upstream server timed out.

505.name: HTTP Version Not Supported
505.description: The server does not support the HTTP protocol version used in the request.
